You said:
Dry-run support?


ChatGPT said:
Yes! âœ… The venafi_cert_renew role fully supports dry-run mode, giving you the ability to simulate the entire renewal workflow without making any changes to the managed systems.

ğŸ” What Is Dry-Run Mode?
In this role, dry-run means:

You check certificate expiry and serials

You generate a full report

You do not download new certs

You do not renew, replace, restart, or cleanup

It allows you to audit certs nearing expiry across all serversâ€”perfect for compliance reporting or scheduled renewals.

ğŸ›ï¸ How to Enable Dry-Run
Set this in vars/main.yml or via extra vars:

yaml
Copy
Edit
report_only: true
Or from the CLI:

bash
Copy
Edit
ansible-playbook playbook.yml -e "report_only=true"
ğŸ” How It's Used Internally
In renew_cert.yml and other write/change tasks, we add:

yaml
Copy
Edit
when: not report_only
So, for example, this task:

yaml
Copy
Edit
- name: "Renew certificates via VCert CLI"
  command: >
    {{ vcert_install_dir }}/vcert renew ...
  when: not report_only
â€¦will skip during dry-run mode.

âœ… What Does Happen in Dry-Run Mode?
Task	Executes?	Notes
VCert CLI Download	âœ…	To allow pickup or inspection
Cert Pickup (if not exists)	âœ…	Reuses existing .pem if found
Cert Expiry Check	âœ…	Uses OpenSSL on local .pem files
HTTPD Config Parsing	âœ…	Extracts Keyfile, Alias, Port
Validity & Serial Matching	âœ…	Confirms current cert serial vs remote
Report Compilation	âœ…	Always compiles & sends summary email
Renewal & Replace	âŒ	Guarded by when: not report_only
Server Restart	âŒ	Handler won't trigger
Cleanup	âŒ	Skipped in dry-run
ğŸ“¬ Sample Email Output (Dry-Run Mode)
yaml
Copy
Edit
Venafi Cert Renewal Report (DRY RUN)
